This is a staging table which contains the persisted measure data. After measure derivation the results will be persisted here for further processing.
Data is truncated based on process id.
Following columns in this table have default values and need not be populated from Measure derivation View (Unless the measure specifically require to populate any of these values).
CNCY_IDNN_BK USGE_CNCY_CATG_IDNN_BK CORT_VERS_N MSUR_QLFY_C
Record identifier Business Key. E.g. For Account domain this will contain ACCT_IDNN_BK For Application domain this will contain APPT_IDNN_BK
List of columns that constitute the Business Key that is stated in RECD_IDNN_BK column split by ‘~’
Source Record No. E.g. In Acct. Domain its Full Account identifier used in the source system as the unique key. In Application Domain its CommSee unique application identifier

In Account Domain this Identifies subsets of accounts within the source system. For example, in the Home loan system the loan and its offset Mortgage Interest Saver Account (MISA) are assigned the same account number. To separately identify these accounts in the Account Domain, Account Qualifier Codes (ACCT_QLFY_C) of 'HL' (home loan) and 'MS' (MISA) are assigned.
Similarly in Application domain it identifies subset of applications.

To identify Subject area. i.e. Account, Application, etc. This will be used to filter data during Hub/Link data load. E.g. Measures with ACCT Subject are will be loaded to H_ACCT and L_ACCT_MSUR_NEW
Valid values are,
ACCT - Account APPT - Application EVNT - Event/Transactions OPPT - Opportunity
More codes will be introduced as an when required.
The date as at the measure derived
Period Type. Valid values are DAY, WKLY or MNTH
Measure code for the count (#) measures
Measure code for the Rate (%) measures
Currency Identifier Business Key. E.g. AUD
Measure Qualifier Code. Captures the CMD subject area
